Art. 30.3. of the Electronic Commerce Law requires suppliers of goods and services ,which use data storage and recovery devices, to clearly and thoroughly inform users and consumers about the use of and purposes regarding the collected data and provide data subjects the ability to object to the use(opt-out) &nbsp;of their personal data through a simple procedure and free of charge.
Other than the rule mentioned above, the current legal framework does not specifically address location data, cookies, local storage objects or other similar data-gathering tools.Last modified 24 Jan 2022
				
			